content:
On April 17, a netizen posted a video saying that he had reported to the Changsha Yuelu District Market Supervision Administration that the "Boworth" company violated the Advertising Law. Not long after, "Boworth" confronted him with his report and all his personal information.
After he posted the video online, the Changsha Yuelu District Market Supervision Administration's Letters and Calls Office called him and said it was unclear whether it was leaked by the unit.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On April 19, the owners of Beijing Changhai Royal Villa Phase 3 collectively issued a "Forced Mortgage Suspension Warning Letter".
The letter stated that because the various departments had previously passed the buck to each other, the owners were disappointed with the implementation of the government's policy of guaranteed delivery of the house. After repeated unsuccessful communications with the government and the developer, it was decided to stop repaying the bank loan from October 31 (the expiration date of the extension agreement) until the house was delivered with guaranteed quality and quantity.
